Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located along Centennial Boulevard, this site lies in the heart of what will be Warman's exclusive primary entrance after the completion of a $60.6 million dollar overpass by the Saskatchewan government, which will filter traffic in from highway 305. The area immediately surrounding Centennial Common will consist of low to medium density residential as well as complementary commercial services and the site is designed to further serve the daily retails needs of the community. Opportunities exist for businesses looking to establish an early presence in a desired location in this growing community.

Preston Centre is a 61,880 SF commercial office-retail complex located on a prominent corner lot at the southwest intersection of 8th Street East and Preston Avenue South within Saskatoon’s Grosvenor Park neighbourhood. The Property benefits from significant volumes of daily automotive and pedestrian traffic, occupying one of the main intersections within southern Saskatoon. Currently, there are two available suites ranging in size from 1,352 to 5,457 SF.

Saskatoon Square is a seventeen-story, Class A office building, centrally located in the downtown core at the intersection of 22nd Street East and 4th Avenue North. With floor to ceiling exterior glazing, the Property offers prominent views of the South Saskatchewan River. The current tenant composition offers a diversified group of national banks, engineering firms, and property management organizations. Major tenants include Vendasta, Scotia Wealth, TD and Tim Horton’s (on the main floor). Surrounding developments are predominantly high-rise and mid-rise office structures with ancillary retail. The Property benefits from its proximity to numerous local restaurants and Midtown Plaza, Saskatoon’s largest regional mall.

CBRE Saskatchewan is pleased to present for lease  ±104,455 SF of Class A office space and ±4,747 SF of main floor retail space at Nutrien Tower - 122 1st  Avenue South. The property is deemed to be one of the most efficient and well-maintained buildings in Saskatoon’s Central Business District. The building features modern finishes, quality buildouts, and 145 underground parking  stalls. Additionally, the main floor is comprised of a retail corridor that connects 1st and 2nd Avenue.With the anticipated move of the property’s owner/operator, Nutrien, the offering presents the rare opportunity to secure building naming rights.
